&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2325&quot; title=&quot;Failure to render OpenType (TrueType)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2325&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2325&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: add log message when it happens&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14123427" author="tilman" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2014 19:25:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test case renders fine by just treating fontfile3 as a TT font. However the spec is much more complex, so I added a log message instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14123736" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2014 22:48:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s the first PDF I&apos;ve seen which uses an OpenType font, interesting to see that it&apos;s from a test suite. I wonder if there are any &quot;real&quot; files out there. The OpenType spec is remarkably complex.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll add support for the subset of OpenType which is equivalent to TrueType and add some warnings if other OTF features are used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
